.TH "ice_devlink_flash_update" 9 "ice_devlink_flash_update" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ice_devlink_flash_update \- Update firmware stored in flash on the device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ice_devlink_flash_update
.BI "(struct devlink *devlink "  ","
.BI "struct devlink_flash_update_params *params "  ","
.BI "struct netlink_ext_ack *extack "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "devlink" 12
pointer to devlink associated with device to update
.IP "params" 12
flash update parameters
.IP "extack" 12
netlink extended ACK structure
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Perform a device flash update. The bulk of the update logic is contained
within the ice_flash_pldm_image function.
.SH "RETURN"
zero on success, or an error code on failure.
